<h1 id="news">News</h1>

<p>Jan, 2025. 2 AISTATS are accpeted!</p>

<p>Nov, 2024. Invited Talk at <a href="https://logmeetupnyc.github.io/">Learning Meets Geometry, Graphs, and Networks
</a>, NY</p>

<p>Jun, 2024. 1 JCGS is accpeted. Federated HMC can be faster than Federated Langevin dynamics.</p>

<p>Apr, 2024. <a href="https://arxiv.org/pdf/2405.04795">Variational Schrödinger Diffusion Models</a> is accepted by ICML’24! Schrödinger diffusion is <strong>scalable</strong> now by linearizing the forward scores. Simulation-free property is all we need for scalability.</p>

<p>Apr, 2024. <a href="https://arxiv.org/pdf/2401.03228">Reflected Schrödinger Bridge</a> is accepted by UAI’24 as <strong>Oral</strong>. Reflected Schrödinger has the linear convergence of couplings via entropic optimal transport on bounded domains.</p>

